            <h2 class="text-center">What happens once I'm accepted?</h2>

            <h3>Congratulations!</h3>

            <p>We'll let you know within 48 hours of your application being accepted. We'll get in touch via email
                and give you details on servers, teamspeak, mod sets and training. We'll also let you know the next
                steps
                for you to get qualified and good to go for our next operation.</p>

            <p>Once you've jumped on to our team speak, a member of our HR Team (J1 Branch) will interview you. They
                will
                be trying to figure out if you have the traits needed to fit in with our current members. It's nothing
                extreme and usually is over in about fifteen to twenty minutes. Once J1 is happy, they will assign
                you the rank of Recruit.</p>

            <p>Once you're a recruit in rank, you'll start downloading our mod set and be given access to our steam
                group.
                We use the steam group to organise and schedule events and training.</p>

            <p>All members of SOCOMD need to qualify on different training programs. Recruits <b>must</b> complete
                a Commando Basic Training Course (CBTC) within four weeks of a successful application - CBTC ensures you
                can
                perform at a basic standard on the battlefield, more advanced training comes after that!</p>

